# Keep LF line endings on files that the runtime parses or runs, even when the
# repo is checked out on a Windows runner (autocrlf would rewrite them with CRLF):
#  - shell scripts: CRLF breaks the shebang/`set` lines.
#  - .marreta source: the lexer is newline/indentation sensitive and rejects \r.
#  - marreta.env: CRLF would append \r to env values (e.g. secret hashes).
*.sh text eol=lf
*.marreta text eol=lf
*.env text eol=lf
marreta.env text eol=lf
